Canadian Prime Minister Justin Trudeau and US Vice President Mike Pence met in Ottawa to discuss various issues, including the ratification process for the United States-Mexico-Canada Trade Agreement (USMCA). Trudeau expressed his optimism about the agreement, calling it a win-win-win for all three countries. They also discussed the challenges they face with China, particularly the arbitrary detention of Canadians. Pence thanked Trudeau for his efforts in driving the USMCA forward and assured him that the US Congress is working towards its approval. They also touched upon the ongoing crisis in Venezuela, with both countries supporting the restoration of democracy. Despite their busy schedule, they joked about the NBA Finals game between the Toronto Raptors and the Golden State Warriors.